About: Popular TikToker and social media star who is best known by her ashleyb4253 TikTok account. She has gained recognition on social media primarily from her lip-syncing, dancing, short comedy, and lifestyle videos with her family and friends.
Before Fame: She was a theater student in high school.
Trivia: She credits Taylor Swift as being one of her favorite music artists. In August of 2023, she was given the opportunity to see Taylor Swift perform live at SoFi Stadium during her Eras Tour. As a result of her popularity, she has received just over 2.4 million followers and 236 million likes on TikTok.
Family Life: She has lived along with her parents and her siblings in New Jersey.
Associated With: She has created TikToks set to music by Michael Bublé and Malcolm Todd.

About: Partnered Twitch broadcaster and social media personality best known for her self-titled channel. She live streams under the platform's "Just Chatting" directory. She has more than 460,000 followers on the platform.
Before Fame: She launched her Twitch channel in March of 2018.
Trivia: One of her channel emotes is inspired by the Animal Crossing character Tom Nook. She has live-streamed gameplay from Super Mario 64. She hosts a Discord server where her fans can chat in real-time with her.
Family Life: She was born in the United States.
Associated With: She posted a TikTok with LuluLuvely at TwitchCon in September 2024.

About: Became widely recognized as the daughter of photographer and YouTube star Jordan Matter.  She built up a large fan base from appearing in videos alongside her father on Instagram and YouTube. She also has her own Instagram account called salishmatter, where she has over 3.2 million followers.
Before Fame: She began to frequently appear on social media in 2020.
Trivia: She appeared in a dancing TikTok set to the Ciara song "Get Up" in February 2020. She became a level seven gymnast. She is vegetarian. She's done several collaborations with Nidal Wonder and she referred to him as her bestie. She launched her own YouTube channel in 2023 and it quickly grew to surpass 1 million subscribers from just a few videos some of which were reaction videos.
Family Life: Her older brother Hudson is a photographer and social media star. Her mom Lauren has appeared in several of her videos. She has a dog named Boomer who has often appeared in her social media.
Associated With: She appeared on her brother's YouTube channel with dancer Rachel Quiner in June 2020.  She's done collaboration videos with many popular YouTube families including The Royalty Family and Matt & Rebecca.

About: Trending social media personality and TikTok content creator best known for her harperzilmer4 account. She shares lip-sync performances and get-ready-with-me content. She has more than 4 million fans on the platform.  She released her debut song "Queen B" on December 26, 2023.
Before Fame: She began posting content on TikTok in January of 2023.  She started her freshman year of high school in August of 2023 and she has been a cheerleader for her school.
Trivia: In February of 2023, one of her get-ready-with-me TikToks went viral with more than 5 million views. She performed a viral lip-sync set to music made famous by the rap duo OutKast. She rose in popularity alongside Maverick and Cash Baker on the LOL Podcast.  She visited New York City in November of 2023 and she thanked Spirit of America Productions for helping to make it happen.
Family Life: Her sister is Reese Zilmer and she's posted several fun Instagram photos with her sister including on in the snow in Colorado in December of 2022. Her mother is often featured in her TikToks, including a January 2024 TikTok from the front seat of the car, where her mother reacts to Harper's dancing.
Associated With: She created a TikTok set to music originally performed by Big Boi and Andre 3000. She and Salish Matter collaborated on a TikTok in December 2023 where they wore '80s clothes.
